1
00:00:39,533 --> 00:00:42,467
<i>Manuel, Jessica,
I miss you both so much!</i>

2
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:44,867
<i> Don't you dare hurt Manuel!</i>

3
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,267
<i> Please stop!</i>

4
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:48,567
<i>Why are you interfering in this
conversation with my husband?</i>

5
00:00:48,700 --> 00:00:51,300
<i>He is married to me,
so I am the legal Mrs. Cruz!</i>

6
00:00:51,433 --> 00:00:52,733
<i> Mommy, can you please stop!</i>

7
00:00:52,867 --> 00:00:55,867
<i>I wanted to be here!
I love it here!</i>

8
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:56,933
<i> Hazel!</i>

9
00:00:57,067 --> 00:00:59,033
<i>Are you still working
for Aunt Felma?</i>

10
00:00:59,167 --> 00:01:00,633
<i> No, I already quit.</i>

11
00:01:00,767 --> 00:01:02,600
<i>How can we even be in the same
room if we're not okay?</i>

12
00:01:02,733 --> 00:01:04,500
<i>Maybe we need
to give each other space.</i>

13
00:01:04,633 --> 00:01:07,933
<i>Just put your clothes
in Mayette's cabinet.</i>

14
00:01:08,100 --> 00:01:09,267
<i>I just needed to ask you,
Andrea...</i>

15
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:11,767
<i> When you left, were you happy?</i>

16
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:12,867
<i> Were you hurt?</i>

17
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,800
<i> Do you need to take medicine?</i>

18
00:01:14,933 --> 00:01:16,967
<i>What's happening around us
hurts me more, Manuel.</i>

19
00:01:17,100 --> 00:01:18,467
<i>I realized
that it is not that easy</i>

20
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:21,400
<i>to let Jeffrey and Andrea
go out on their own.</i>

21
00:01:21,533 --> 00:01:24,700
<i>This is Atty. Nico Salazar.
He's an expert on family code.</i>

22
00:01:24,833 --> 00:01:25,933
<i>I will go straight to the point.</i>

23
00:01:26,067 --> 00:01:27,633
<i>I want to file a complaint
against my husband</i>

24
00:01:27,767 --> 00:01:29,200
<i> for kidnapping my daughter.</i>

25
00:01:29,333 --> 00:01:31,333
<i> Don't frown, Mommy Pretty!</i>

26
00:01:31,467 --> 00:01:33,333
<i> Daddy's here.</i>

27
00:01:33,467 --> 00:01:35,100
<i> Andrea is here.</i>

28
00:01:35,233 --> 00:01:36,133
<i> Oh, thank goodness!</i>

29
00:01:36,267 --> 00:01:38,500
<i>I have to go.
She might hear me talking.</i>

30
00:01:38,633 --> 00:01:39,667
<i> Andrea is safe.</i>

31
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,533
<i> Abel will take care of her.</i>

32
00:01:41,700 --> 00:01:44,067
<i>At least Jeffrey is with Daisy.</i>

33
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,967
<i>I hope you can patch things up
with him.</i>

34
00:01:46,100 --> 00:01:47,033
<i> I will not be able to tolerate</i>

35
00:01:47,167 --> 00:01:48,367
<i>this situation
with your siblings.</i>

36
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:51,267
<i>Ma'am, Jeff sent me
a text message.</i>

37
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:54,467
<i>He wants to pack
Andrea's remaining stuff.</i>

38
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:55,733
<i> Should I do it?</i>

39
00:02:06,333 --> 00:02:06,900
Jeff...

40
00:02:07,333 --> 00:02:08,133
Here.

41
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:09,700
Your stuff is here.

42
00:02:09,833 --> 00:02:12,500
I asked Didang to pack the rest
of your stuff at home.

43
00:02:12,833 --> 00:02:13,900
I had them picked up as well.

44
00:02:14,067 --> 00:02:15,067
Thank you.

45
00:02:16,733 --> 00:02:19,467
How are you doing at Daisy
and Tetay's place?

46
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:20,800
Fine.

47
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:22,200
How about you?

48
00:02:23,067 --> 00:02:23,967
Are you good?

49
00:02:24,533 --> 00:02:26,600
Are you sure uncle approves
of having you here?

50
00:02:27,367 --> 00:02:28,200
Yeah.

51
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:33,233
They said I can stay
until whenever.

52
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,333
But of course,

53
00:02:35,467 --> 00:02:36,833
I still plan on moving out

54
00:02:36,967 --> 00:02:39,833
as soon as I find
another place to crash in.

55
00:02:41,133 --> 00:02:42,667
Are you not going to work?

56
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:44,567
What?

57
00:02:45,300 --> 00:02:46,333
What for?

58
00:02:49,567 --> 00:02:51,067
Mom and I will be both
in the office.

59
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:52,667
I don't want
to start fighting again.

60
00:02:53,533 --> 00:02:55,867
I will just send them
my resignation letter.

61
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:58,333
How about you?

62
00:02:59,033 --> 00:03:00,900
I don't want to see mom, either.

63
00:03:02,233 --> 00:03:03,233
I don't want to fight, either.

64
00:03:05,367 --> 00:03:06,367
But...

65
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:07,800
What?

66
00:03:09,767 --> 00:03:11,800
It just feels different
to be away from her.

67
00:03:12,633 --> 00:03:13,867
It's the first time
this has happened.

68
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,333
So, are you having
second thoughts?

69
00:03:17,467 --> 00:03:20,500
I was just thinking that
maybe we made a hasty decision.

70
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:21,633
I don't care!

71
00:03:22,033 --> 00:03:23,600
As for me,
I know I'm doing well!

72
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:26,133
I would rather be...

73
00:03:26,633 --> 00:03:29,367
away from mom
and not be with her,

74
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:32,000
than see your father
and his child!

75
00:03:47,667 --> 00:03:50,000
Daddy, when you bring me
to school tomorrow,

76
00:03:50,133 --> 00:03:52,567
I would introduce you
to my classmates!

77
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:55,300
I want them to believe me
that I really have a father.

78
00:03:55,467 --> 00:03:56,733
Yes, sure!

79
00:03:57,433 --> 00:03:58,467
Do you want me
to fetch you as well?

80
00:03:58,600 --> 00:04:00,300
But after work, okay?

81
00:04:01,367 --> 00:04:02,633
What do you do at work, Dad?

82
00:04:07,267 --> 00:04:10,300
Your dad is working as
a deliveryman for Mommy Pretty.

83
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:13,167
Daddy, I thought you stopped
working there?

84
00:04:14,333 --> 00:04:16,100
I am just worried

85
00:04:16,233 --> 00:04:18,667
that the tasks assigned to me
were not turned over properly.

86
00:04:21,267 --> 00:04:23,967
It's quite obvious
that you care about your job.

87
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:26,667
Maybe you do not have to resign.

88
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,433
I told you I need space.

89
00:04:34,033 --> 00:04:36,000
I am sure that's what
my mom wants as well.

90
00:04:36,533 --> 00:04:38,000
Oh no, Dad!

91
00:04:38,133 --> 00:04:40,133
Mommy Pretty misses you so much!

92
00:04:43,433 --> 00:04:44,333
How can you say so, Dear?

93
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:48,033
I just thought about it.

94
00:04:48,533 --> 00:04:51,500
No mom can let go of their child
just like that.

95
00:04:51,933 --> 00:04:55,233
I am sure Mommy Pretty
misses you.

96
00:04:55,367 --> 00:04:56,267
Right, Mommy?

97
00:05:05,267 --> 00:05:07,433
If I order longganisa,

98
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,767
how can I transport this
to Batangas?

99
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:12,033
That's where I plan
on selling this.

100
00:05:12,167 --> 00:05:14,900
You have to put everything
in a styrofoam.

101
00:05:15,033 --> 00:05:16,633
We will provide everything
for you.

102
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:18,267
We'll take care of it.

103
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,600
Oh, all right.

104
00:05:20,233 --> 00:05:22,233
Ma'am Paz, excuse me...

105
00:05:23,167 --> 00:05:24,767
Ma'am, will you excuse me
for a moment?

106
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:28,100
JRP Supermarket called.

107
00:05:28,233 --> 00:05:30,200
They wanted to follow up
about the requirements

108
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:33,133
for our product launch
in their store.

109
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,300
What product launch?

110
00:05:35,833 --> 00:05:38,533
Ma'am Andrea arranged this.

111
00:05:41,367 --> 00:05:42,867
I have no idea.

112
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,067
What is that?

113
00:05:45,167 --> 00:05:49,233
We have to deliver the products
to their Parañaque branch

114
00:05:49,367 --> 00:05:51,100
before the week ends.

115
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:56,500
Jeffrey is in charge
of that area.

116
00:05:56,633 --> 00:05:57,767
Maybe he knows about this.

117
00:05:58,533 --> 00:05:59,467
Jeffrey?

118
00:06:00,033 --> 00:06:01,933
Oh, he did not show up for work.

119
00:06:02,467 --> 00:06:03,767
I think he resigned.

120
00:06:03,900 --> 00:06:05,867
Just like Andrea.

121
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,467
I just got her email.

122
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:10,433
Let's talk about this later.

123
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:12,900
Ma'am, I apologize. Excuse me.

124
00:06:13,033 --> 00:06:15,433
I will get back to you later,
okay?

125
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:20,233
Friend, I am sorry.

126
00:06:20,367 --> 00:06:21,900
I did not know.

127
00:06:24,033 --> 00:06:26,833
You also did not tell me
that she moved in with you.

128
00:06:27,433 --> 00:06:28,633
Oh, Paz.

129
00:06:30,533 --> 00:06:31,533
But, Felma...

130
00:06:31,667 --> 00:06:34,867
I was going to tell you,
but Abel got ahead of me.

131
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:37,933
I thought they will
treat work separately.

132
00:06:38,067 --> 00:06:41,300
I thought this would only
be our personal problem.

133
00:06:42,233 --> 00:06:43,733
By the way, Felma,

134
00:06:43,867 --> 00:06:45,633
Didang called me.

135
00:06:45,767 --> 00:06:47,300
She said she cannot reach
your phone.

136
00:06:47,433 --> 00:06:52,900
She said Manuel will go
to our place to visit Andrea.

137
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:59,567
<i>Friend, Felma's kids moved out!</i>

138
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:12,100
She deserves that!

139
00:07:12,533 --> 00:07:14,500
She kidnapped...

140
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,833
my daughter,

141
00:07:17,900 --> 00:07:19,433
and now she got her karma!

142
00:07:21,267 --> 00:07:23,633
She should wait...

143
00:07:24,667 --> 00:07:26,500
for my revenge, too!

144
00:07:45,367 --> 00:07:46,433
Manuel!

145
00:07:46,967 --> 00:07:48,700
I just informed you
that your daughter is here.

146
00:07:48,867 --> 00:07:50,767
I did not tell you to come over!

147
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:52,800
- Uncle?
- I just wanted to...

148
00:08:03,467 --> 00:08:05,500
I already asked you...

149
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,267
I am sorry, Andrea.

150
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:08,800
Andrea, do not be mad
at your uncle.

151
00:08:08,933 --> 00:08:10,467
He just wanted to help.

152
00:08:12,133 --> 00:08:13,033
Besides...

153
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:16,500
Dear, I was also hoping
that you were no longer angry.

154
00:08:17,533 --> 00:08:19,200
I feel sorry for your mom.

155
00:08:19,667 --> 00:08:22,267
This is so hard for her
that the two of you left her.

156
00:08:23,767 --> 00:08:24,500
Okay.

157
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:27,233
I will move back in.

158
00:08:28,933 --> 00:08:30,500
If you and Jessica
are moving out.

159
00:08:31,667 --> 00:08:34,200
Aunt Felma allowed us to stay!

160
00:08:36,300 --> 00:08:38,300
Daddy is talking to you nicely.

161
00:08:38,433 --> 00:08:40,000
Why can't you meet halfway?

162
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:43,000
And who are you
to tell me what to do?

163
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:44,867
Dear, stop talking back.

164
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,700
Dad, this is getting annoying!

165
00:08:47,333 --> 00:08:50,567
You've been humble and
apologetic for the longest time!

166
00:08:51,233 --> 00:08:53,167
But she still won't give in!

167
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:55,400
Because your father left me.

168
00:08:57,933 --> 00:08:59,067
He left me.

169
00:09:01,067 --> 00:09:03,333
If you go through everything
I did,

170
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:07,000
I don't know, I bet your heart
wouldn't turn to stone, too.

171
00:09:08,733 --> 00:09:09,967
I get it.

172
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:12,400
I get why you left.

173
00:09:13,233 --> 00:09:14,567
<i> You're leaving?</i>

174
00:09:18,833 --> 00:09:19,600
<i> Darling...</i>

175
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,400
<i> this is for you.</i>

176
00:09:23,367 --> 00:09:25,267
<i>So we can afford
your medical bills.</i>

177
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:27,733
<i>I promise that I will never ever
run again!</i>

178
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:30,567
<i>I will never run out of breath,</i>

179
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:32,533
<i>so that I don't have
to go through an operation...</i>

180
00:09:32,667 --> 00:09:34,600
<i>So that you don't have
to go away.</i>

181
00:09:34,733 --> 00:09:36,700
<i>I only have
a temporary contract.</i>

182
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:37,833
<i> Once I have already saved up,</i>

183
00:09:37,967 --> 00:09:39,100
<i>I will come back home
immediately!</i>

184
00:09:40,933 --> 00:09:42,667
So that you can afford
my medication.

185
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:44,700
So that I can have
that operation.

186
00:09:46,567 --> 00:09:50,100
But you do not know how many
times I blamed myself!

187
00:09:51,567 --> 00:09:53,000
I wish I did not have
to be sick.

188
00:09:55,733 --> 00:09:57,600
If I were not sick,
you would not leave.

189
00:09:58,267 --> 00:09:59,567
You would not have met
that woman!

190
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:00,767
You would have never left us!

191
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:03,367
Andrea...

192
00:10:06,433 --> 00:10:07,933
My daughter, please
do not blame yourself.

193
00:10:08,067 --> 00:10:09,367
It's not your fault!

194
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:12,600
You made my heart feel better.

195
00:10:14,333 --> 00:10:16,300
But you also hardened it
when you left us.

196
00:10:18,067 --> 00:10:19,433
You abandoned me.

197
00:10:22,167 --> 00:10:23,133
Andrea, my daughter...

198
00:10:24,767 --> 00:10:26,233
Dear, I am already here...

199
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:30,533
Please let me make up
for the lost time...

200
00:10:32,933 --> 00:10:35,333
Let me melt your cold heart.

201
00:10:36,567 --> 00:10:38,633
I want to become
a good father to you again.

202
00:10:39,667 --> 00:10:40,267
How?

203
00:10:41,733 --> 00:10:43,067
You were gone for a long time.

204
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:47,333
I have no idea how to become
a daughter anymore.

205
00:11:15,433 --> 00:11:17,033
<i> My god, Manuel!</i>

206
00:11:17,667 --> 00:11:19,800
I already told you!

207
00:11:20,567 --> 00:11:23,500
Andrea needs time!

208
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,567
Why did you go to her?

209
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,600
Felma, I feel sorry for you.

210
00:11:29,433 --> 00:11:30,467
You are so sad.

211
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:32,500
You've been having a hard time
being away from them.

212
00:11:32,633 --> 00:11:34,133
It's impossible for Manuel
not to do anything.

213
00:11:34,267 --> 00:11:35,433
<i> He is their father!</i>

214
00:11:36,467 --> 00:11:37,400
If that were me,

215
00:11:37,633 --> 00:11:38,433
if that was our family
that's been having a hard time,

216
00:11:38,567 --> 00:11:40,133
I would find a way
to patch things up!

217
00:11:40,267 --> 00:11:42,700
But you should not
have told Manuel!

218
00:11:42,967 --> 00:11:46,833
You already know him so deeply!
He will act without thinking!

219
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:49,333
<i>You should have given it
a lot of thought</i>

220
00:11:49,467 --> 00:11:51,100
before you went there
and talked to her!

221
00:11:51,733 --> 00:11:53,467
What do you think I did?

222
00:11:54,233 --> 00:11:55,900
That was all that I could do

223
00:11:56,033 --> 00:11:58,033
because I am stuck
in this wheelchair!

224
00:11:59,567 --> 00:12:01,067
Do you know how hard it is
for me to accept

225
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:03,833
that I cannot do anything
for my family?

226
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:07,933
And I am the main reason
why you have gone your own way!

227
00:12:08,367 --> 00:12:09,967
That's why I am doing the best
that I can

228
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:11,667
to bring them back here!

229
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:14,400
You should have asked me first!

230
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:16,867
You should not have gone
there without asking me!

231
00:12:17,633 --> 00:12:20,033
<i>You talk as if
you do not gossip!</i>

232
00:12:20,167 --> 00:12:22,267
You also told everything
to Felma, right?

233
00:12:22,933 --> 00:12:25,167
I am so sure you told her
Andrea is here.

234
00:12:25,300 --> 00:12:27,400
But of course, I did!

235
00:12:27,533 --> 00:12:30,367
Because my friend uses
her brain!

236
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:33,500
And she knows how to handle
things properly!

237
00:12:35,433 --> 00:12:38,133
I appreciate your effort,
Manuel!

238
00:12:39,267 --> 00:12:40,567
But...

239
00:12:41,333 --> 00:12:42,833
you don't know them anymore!

240
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,800
They are no longer young kids

241
00:12:45,467 --> 00:12:47,233
that you can ask politely!

242
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:48,767
Especially Andrea!

243
00:12:49,467 --> 00:12:50,600
She has grown!

244
00:12:52,033 --> 00:12:53,767
Time passed,
and she toughened up!

245
00:12:54,633 --> 00:12:56,033
You did not know that!

246
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:57,833
Because you were gone
for a long time!

247
00:13:01,333 --> 00:13:02,433
Felma, I know.

248
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:05,000
I know that I am the challenge
that you were talking about.

249
00:13:05,133 --> 00:13:07,533
I know I am the reason
why she became like that.

250
00:13:08,067 --> 00:13:09,200
I know that!

251
00:13:10,267 --> 00:13:11,967
If I only knew this is how
things would turn out,

252
00:13:12,100 --> 00:13:13,967
I would not have gone abroad!

253
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:16,567
I should have just tired myself
out from working until I die!

254
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:20,200
Because I know I am dead
to them now, anyway!

255
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:26,067
I should have
just killed myself!

256
00:13:38,867 --> 00:13:40,033
Let's stop this.

257
00:13:40,833 --> 00:13:42,833
Please do not blame yourself.

258
00:13:45,833 --> 00:13:47,467
We have already forgiven
each other.

259
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:50,733
Someday...

260
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:54,767
your kids will also forgive you.

261
00:14:21,233 --> 00:14:21,933
Are you still...

262
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:23,933
Are you still mad at me?

263
00:14:24,067 --> 00:14:26,100
- Oh, I don't know!
- I'm sorry...

264
00:14:26,667 --> 00:14:28,900
I already told you,
you should consult with me first

265
00:14:29,067 --> 00:14:32,300
before you say things
to your friend!

266
00:14:33,533 --> 00:14:34,500
I promise...

267
00:14:36,533 --> 00:14:37,767
It's baby time!

268
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:40,167
Baby time?

269
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:43,133
It's all your fault!

270
00:14:43,967 --> 00:14:45,367
You do not deserve baby time!

271
00:14:45,767 --> 00:14:47,033
Let's go
and have some baby time!

272
00:14:47,167 --> 00:14:48,133
But...

273
00:14:49,033 --> 00:14:50,133
Hey...

274
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:52,367
- where are you going?
- You don't have to go!

275
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:53,033
- It's fine.
- Where are you going?

276
00:14:53,167 --> 00:14:55,033
You don't have to go!

277
00:15:03,833 --> 00:15:05,067
It's okay.

278
00:15:05,733 --> 00:15:08,667
If I stay here longer,

279
00:15:09,533 --> 00:15:12,600
he might come back again...

280
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:16,133
I am so sorry, Andrea.

281
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:19,633
I just want them
to stop worrying.

282
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:21,800
I am also a father.

283
00:15:21,933 --> 00:15:25,200
I know the feeling of not
knowing where your kids are.

284
00:15:26,733 --> 00:15:30,333
I'm sorry for dragging you
into this.

285
00:15:30,900 --> 00:15:33,333
So it's better for me to go.

286
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:35,933
- Oh, here's my ride.
- Wait, Andrea...

287
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:37,400
Where will you go?

288
00:15:38,833 --> 00:15:41,100
I've found a place.

289
00:15:42,267 --> 00:15:44,067
Thanks for everything.

290
00:15:44,433 --> 00:15:46,100
Thank you.

291
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:48,900
Let me help you.

292
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:03,867
Take care.

293
00:16:11,333 --> 00:16:14,500
- Take care, okay?
- Auntie, thank you.

294
00:16:14,867 --> 00:16:15,900
Take care.

295
00:16:47,033 --> 00:16:47,800
Ma'am...

296
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:52,200
how sure are you
that we will see them here?

297
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:54,900
Actually, I'm not sure.

298
00:16:55,667 --> 00:16:57,100
That's why we're waiting.

299
00:16:58,433 --> 00:17:01,733
But this would take so much
of our time.

300
00:17:04,067 --> 00:17:06,000
Attorney, what are you
complaining about?

301
00:17:07,700 --> 00:17:09,733
We will just threaten them.

302
00:17:10,933 --> 00:17:12,833
You should thank me, actually.

303
00:17:13,367 --> 00:17:14,733
I am paying you per hour.

304
00:17:17,167 --> 00:17:18,700
Ma'am, I want to make this
clear, okay?

305
00:17:19,967 --> 00:17:21,367
I am willing to help you...

306
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:25,733
but only within legal bounds.

307
00:17:26,600 --> 00:17:29,100
I will not cross the line,
I hope that is clear.

308
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,833
Okay. You know what, Jessica,

309
00:17:40,967 --> 00:17:44,667
we can book easily here
because of the reception.

310
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:47,100
Do you want to go to the mall?

311
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:50,200
We need a breather!

312
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:52,200
Sorry, Sis.

313
00:17:52,333 --> 00:17:53,900
Mommy is really harsh.

314
00:17:54,767 --> 00:17:56,833
I don't mind.

315
00:17:57,933 --> 00:17:59,833
Oh, look at that!

316
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:03,867
Or do you want to have milk tea?

317
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:08,300
I know a coffee shop nearby,
and they make the best milk tea!

318
00:18:08,433 --> 00:18:09,600
<i> Sure, Sis!</i>

319
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:19,000
- Jessica...
- Mommy!

320
00:18:19,133 --> 00:18:20,867
What are you doing here?

321
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:22,933
Darling, I was hoping
we could talk.

322
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:25,567
Just for a moment...

323
00:18:25,700 --> 00:18:27,800
This is Atty. Salazar.

324
00:18:28,633 --> 00:18:30,200
He wants to explain something.

325
00:18:30,333 --> 00:18:31,367
Attorney.

326
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:32,867
- Why are you with a lawyer?
- This is my daughter.

327
00:18:34,033 --> 00:18:37,233
Jessica, I just want to explain
something.

328
00:18:37,367 --> 00:18:39,733
Your mom consulted me

329
00:18:39,867 --> 00:18:43,900
and told me that your father
took you away from her

330
00:18:44,033 --> 00:18:45,300
without her consent,

331
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:49,667
so she has to file a kidnapping
complaint against your dad.

332
00:18:55,167 --> 00:18:55,967
What?

333
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:59,700
No! Daddy did not kidnap me!

334
00:18:59,833 --> 00:19:02,033
And please do not drag
my mother into this mess!

335
00:19:02,767 --> 00:19:05,100
Oh, please. Don't interfere
in our discussion!

336
00:19:05,667 --> 00:19:08,000
Are we talking to you?

337
00:19:08,933 --> 00:19:11,567
Let's not make a scene here.

338
00:19:14,033 --> 00:19:14,700
Dear,

339
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:17,100
we will just talk to you.

340
00:19:17,233 --> 00:19:19,967
Maybe it's better
if we just talk inside the van.

341
00:19:20,100 --> 00:19:21,467
So we can talk properly.

342
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:23,433
Is it okay? We will be quick.

343
00:19:23,567 --> 00:19:25,433
No. I will not go with you.

344
00:19:26,567 --> 00:19:27,600
Dear...

345
00:19:28,467 --> 00:19:30,600
the attorney just has
to explain something to you.

346
00:19:30,733 --> 00:19:32,400
It will just be quick.
It will be a quick talk.

347
00:19:32,533 --> 00:19:33,967
I just want to clear things up.

348
00:19:34,100 --> 00:19:35,400
Jessica...

349
00:19:36,267 --> 00:19:38,033
do not worry. I will mediate.

350
00:19:40,733 --> 00:19:41,700
Jessica...

351
00:19:46,300 --> 00:19:47,533
It's okay, Sis.

352
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:50,767
We will just talk.

353
00:20:14,333 --> 00:20:15,267
At last,

354
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:16,600
you are with me now!

355
00:20:17,100 --> 00:20:19,067
Driver, let's go!

356
00:20:20,267 --> 00:20:21,933
Start the van now!

357
00:20:22,533 --> 00:20:25,800
What do you mean? I thought
we would just talk, Mom?

358
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:27,567
Shut up! Lock the door.

359
00:20:27,700 --> 00:20:30,533
Driver, do not listen to her!

360
00:20:30,667 --> 00:20:34,267
Mrs. Cruz, this was not part
of the plan.

361
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,367
Mom, let me go!

362
00:20:36,533 --> 00:20:37,167
No.

363
00:20:37,300 --> 00:20:38,233
No!

364
00:20:39,867 --> 00:20:41,033
This one's for you.

365
00:20:41,867 --> 00:20:47,933
If you're bored, you can
actually go out and watch TV.

366
00:20:48,433 --> 00:20:49,500
Thank you, Didang!

367
00:20:52,567 --> 00:20:53,333
<i> Didang?</i>

368
00:20:53,467 --> 00:20:55,067
Yes, Ma'am Felma.

369
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:58,300
- Miss, miss.
- Manuel, excuse me.

370
00:20:58,433 --> 00:21:00,300
Didang, why did you not arrange
the things

371
00:21:00,433 --> 00:21:02,433
we're supposed to bring
to the office?

372
00:21:02,567 --> 00:21:04,200
Oh, it slipped my mind!

373
00:21:04,333 --> 00:21:06,633
Okay, I will arrange them now.

374
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:09,867
Hello, Coleen?

375
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:10,933
Mom!

376
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:13,367
Jessica was kidnapped
by her mom!

377
00:21:13,733 --> 00:21:15,300
We are here at Gate 2!

378
00:21:15,433 --> 00:21:16,167
What?

379
00:21:16,433 --> 00:21:18,000
Okay. I will go there now.

380
00:21:18,133 --> 00:21:20,433
Look after your sister, okay?

381
00:21:20,567 --> 00:21:22,467
Mom, you have to hurry! Please!

382
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:25,600
What happened to Jessica?

383
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:28,767
Hazel kidnapped Jessica.

384
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:30,233
I will go with you!

385
00:21:30,367 --> 00:21:32,200
Don't bother.

386
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:33,300
I got this.

387
00:21:33,433 --> 00:21:35,200
I will bring Jessica home.

388
00:21:36,433 --> 00:21:37,333
Take care!

389
00:21:37,467 --> 00:21:39,067
- Thank you.
- Ma'am, be safe.

390
00:21:40,167 --> 00:21:45,100
Sir, we have to pray
that Jessica will be safe.

391
00:21:49,333 --> 00:21:50,933
You will not go with me?

392
00:21:51,067 --> 00:21:52,800
I won't go with you!

393
00:21:52,933 --> 00:21:54,133
If you don't come with me,

394
00:21:54,267 --> 00:21:55,833
I will file that case
against your dad!

395
00:21:56,433 --> 00:21:58,933
Do you want to know
the punishment for kidnapping?

396
00:21:59,067 --> 00:22:00,133
Attorney, let her know!

397
00:22:02,500 --> 00:22:04,333
Reclusion perpetua,

398
00:22:04,467 --> 00:22:06,733
or life imprisonment!

399
00:22:07,333 --> 00:22:10,467
Twenty years,
or up to 40 years in jail.

400
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:13,267
That means your father
will rot in jail!

401
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:15,133
That's where he will age
and die!

402
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:16,433
Do you want that?

403
00:22:16,567 --> 00:22:17,600
Your father will be imprisoned
for life!

404
00:22:17,733 --> 00:22:18,967
Is that what you want?

405
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:20,600
Mom...

406
00:22:20,733 --> 00:22:23,567
Mom, please,
don't do this to dad...

407
00:22:23,700 --> 00:22:24,867
Please...

408
00:22:25,467 --> 00:22:27,333
So you have to come with me!

409
00:22:27,467 --> 00:22:29,200
- Driver, start the van!
- No!

410
00:22:29,333 --> 00:22:31,833
- Don't, driver! No!
- What are you doing?

411
00:22:31,967 --> 00:22:35,700
You should be on my side!
You are paid here!

412
00:22:35,833 --> 00:22:38,833
- Driver, start the van!
- No! Please!

413
00:22:38,967 --> 00:22:41,533
I don't want to be away
from my dad!

414
00:22:41,667 --> 00:22:43,400
You will not be taken away
because I know

415
00:22:43,533 --> 00:22:45,433
he will follow you!

416
00:22:45,567 --> 00:22:47,067
So you have to go with me, dear.

417
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:48,233
Come with me!

418
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:49,800
Start the van!

419
00:22:49,933 --> 00:22:51,167
Let me go!

420
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:53,400
Nobody leaves!

421
00:22:53,533 --> 00:22:56,433
Don't listen to them!
I'm the one who's paying you!

422
00:22:56,567 --> 00:22:57,867
Jessica!

423
00:22:58,000 --> 00:22:59,200
Do it now!

424
00:22:59,333 --> 00:23:00,200
Shut up!

425
00:23:00,333 --> 00:23:01,333
- Mrs. Cruz!
- Mommy, no!

426
00:23:01,467 --> 00:23:03,933
Aunt Felma, help me!

427
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:05,400
Jessica!

428
00:23:05,533 --> 00:23:07,733
Hazel, let her out!

429
00:23:08,367 --> 00:23:09,367
- Jessica!
- Please don't do this.

430
00:23:09,500 --> 00:23:10,300
Hazel!

431
00:23:10,433 --> 00:23:11,700
Hazel!

432
00:23:11,833 --> 00:23:13,800
Jessica!

433
00:23:13,933 --> 00:23:16,033
Stop mommy! Help me!

434
00:23:16,167 --> 00:23:17,067
Don't hurt her!

435
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:18,467
Driver!

436
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:19,833
Aunt Felma!

437
00:23:19,967 --> 00:23:21,167
Jessica!

438
00:23:24,367 --> 00:23:25,433
What did you do?

439
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:27,267
Did you hurt her again?

440
00:23:27,633 --> 00:23:29,100
You act as if...

441
00:23:29,833 --> 00:23:31,300
you are her mother!

442
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:33,300
And as if you are innocent?

443
00:23:33,433 --> 00:23:35,833
You are an apprentice
to the kidnapping crime!

444
00:23:36,133 --> 00:23:38,933
Attorney, she is
my husband's mistress.

445
00:23:41,633 --> 00:23:44,133
Wow! I am amazed by your guts.

446
00:23:44,600 --> 00:23:46,867
You even brought a lawyer
with you?

447
00:23:47,900 --> 00:23:50,500
Yes. Because I will file
a complaint against you.

448
00:23:51,667 --> 00:23:53,233
You're an accessory
to the crime!

449
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:55,067
You knew!

450
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:57,333
You knew that Manuel
would kidnap Jessica.

451
00:23:57,500 --> 00:23:59,200
And you helped him!

452
00:23:59,700 --> 00:24:02,700
Because you all wanted
to be together?

453
00:24:03,467 --> 00:24:05,133
You are a good scriptwriter.

454
00:24:06,533 --> 00:24:08,133
What do you think
all this is?

455
00:24:08,267 --> 00:24:09,600
Is this not kidnapping?

456
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:11,867
Prove that in court!

457
00:24:12,133 --> 00:24:13,900
Mom! Please stop this!

458
00:24:14,467 --> 00:24:16,467
Aunt Felma did nothing wrong!

459
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:20,000
All she did was to offer
her home to protect us

460
00:24:20,267 --> 00:24:21,267
from you!

461
00:24:22,633 --> 00:24:24,067
Dear...

462
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:25,400
I would not have done
that to you

463
00:24:25,533 --> 00:24:27,533
if you had only followed
what I said.

464
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:31,067
I am sorry.

465
00:24:31,200 --> 00:24:32,667
Please forgive me.

466
00:24:33,967 --> 00:24:35,733
I love you so much...

467
00:24:37,100 --> 00:24:39,233
Dear, fine.

468
00:24:39,367 --> 00:24:40,833
I did something wrong.

469
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:43,500
Yes, I have done a lot
of mistakes.

470
00:24:43,633 --> 00:24:46,900
But no one is perfect, right?

471
00:24:47,700 --> 00:24:49,500
Please give me another chance.

472
00:24:49,633 --> 00:24:50,500
Please?

473
00:24:50,900 --> 00:24:52,600
To be a mother to you.

474
00:24:53,067 --> 00:24:55,567
Dear, I will not ask you
to choose.

475
00:24:56,667 --> 00:24:59,933
I will let you decide if...

476
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:02,233
you come with me.

477
00:25:03,367 --> 00:25:04,400
I promise you...

478
00:25:04,867 --> 00:25:06,733
a new beginning.

479
00:25:07,033 --> 00:25:08,833
We will start anew.

480
00:25:09,433 --> 00:25:10,833
That I promise you.

481
00:25:12,167 --> 00:25:13,900
Or will you go with that woman?

482
00:25:14,433 --> 00:25:15,400
Dear, please.

483
00:25:16,933 --> 00:25:17,800
Please?

484
00:25:20,867 --> 00:25:23,633
How is my most beautiful
princess?

485
00:25:23,767 --> 00:25:25,067
You know what, Mommy Pretty?

486
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:28,000
Daddy brings me to school,
and he also fetches me.

487
00:25:28,133 --> 00:25:30,500
Sometimes, he also prepares
my snacks.

488
00:25:30,633 --> 00:25:31,633
Who is that?

489
00:25:31,767 --> 00:25:36,633
Ladies and gentlemen,
presenting our guest today!

490
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:38,433
Ma'am C!

491
00:25:38,933 --> 00:25:40,067
Thank you, Karla.

492
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:44,833
What is this very hot issue
that you want justice for?

493
00:25:45,233 --> 00:25:46,700
This is about a woman

494
00:25:47,233 --> 00:25:49,167
who is taking my husband away
from me.

495
00:25:49,633 --> 00:25:51,333
And she also brainwashes
my child.

496
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:53,333
She is ruining your name!

497
00:25:53,467 --> 00:25:56,367
She wants the people
to boycott our products!

498
00:25:56,500 --> 00:25:58,833
Hazel, please stop
ruining my wife's name!

499
00:25:59,100 --> 00:26:00,533
I am your wife!

500
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:03,200
Felma made me feel
like a husband!

501
00:26:03,833 --> 00:26:05,167
I will see you in court!

502
00:26:05,733 --> 00:26:08,100
Wait for your subpoena.
